args:
The prince and the apostles hurry the survivors
aboard the landship to get them clear of Grams.
Meanwhile, when Pinon encounters Sandalphon
in the sewers and learns the angels may yet be
revived, she races off to a secret laboratory.
I was flung to another world, where I glimpsed\nthe world overseen by the Progenitor.
There, those born into misery are permitted no\nchance to claim happiness through their efforts.\nThe very idea of possibility does not exist.
It was a thought I could not abide, so I hung\nmy hopes on Satan's power, never knowing\nhow grave a mistake it was...
I still sense the Auspex's will within the\nDemonlord, but the dissolution of her soul\nis only a matter of time.
Saaatan, why're you just staaanding there?\nI'm booored!
Ah, Lilith. Have the wounds you suffered\nat the apostles' hands healed?
Excuse me, but I was better FOREVER ago.\nAlso, all these little skirmishes suck—\nfrom now on, I'm goin' hog wild!
So what's the plan, Loki? You just gonna\nsit here with him or what?
My place is at my lord's side. Besides,\nI've come up with an amusement to pass\nthe time. I'm just getting things ready now.
Oh, but please invite the other demons to\ndo their worst, for their violence feeds the\nDemonlord's power.

I don't take orders from you! ...Ugh.
Can't believe I'm finally free of that stupid
angel body and stupid Loki is STILL ruining
my stupid mood!
Angel's body? Ah, yes. Tell me, what\nbecame of those mimicries after all\nof you were released?
Eh, I dunno. Are you done talking yet?\nActually, know what? Don't care.\nI'm out like a light, bud. Byeeee!
I suppose one can't be too careful...
I have a little errand for all of you\ndemonic entities...
The Gran Fiore's standing by just outside\nGrams, and we're securing a safe route\nfrom the evacuation site as we speak.
Retreat preparations are complete!\nJust give the order, Highness!
In that case, I need all of you to get those\nrefugees on the ship. I'm going to survey\nthe city with the apostles.
There's room on the landship for everyone,\nso please proceed quickly and calmly.
The Watch gave you clear instructions, sir.\nNow kindly shut up and follow them.
A crowded, shared room is unacceptable!\nHere in Grams, one's station in the Canon\naffords a person certain privileges.

It's always the same with you nobles and
your Canon! You don't do a damned thing,
then you strut around like everybody owes
you some kind of favor!
Why, you impertinent wretch! How dare a\nlowlife like yourself even speak to me?!
Enough! We don't have time for this!
Don't try to stop me, apostle! These noble\ntypes will never learn unless you pound a\nlesson into their thick skulls!
Social standing means nothing when\nweighed against the lives of both\nourselves and those we hold dear.
You. Nobleman. The Watch holds all lives\nin equal esteem, and we are attempting to\nsave as many as we can here.
I'm sure you have your own circumstances,\nbut as this is an emergency, I ask your\ncooperation in the name of decency.
And you. Take a look around. It's past time\nto cast aside yesterday's resentments.
Apologies, sir. With all that's happening,\nI lost control there for a second.

And perhaps I was in the wrong as well.
I have a sickly granddaughter with me,
you see, and I merely hoped to secure
her a private room.

I will take any accommodations you wish,
but I ask you to put her in a quiet place.
She has just lost her father, and the shock
of the incident has worsened her condition.
Then you should stay with her. I'll try to\nget you in a cabin close to the sickbay.

You look fatigued, Pinon, and I can only
assume you have been working without
pause for some time. Please, leave the
rest of this to me.
You're very kind, but I can't do that.\nMy time is limited, so I need to—
Respectfully, I understand your hurry. \nBut a moment's rest can oft permit us to\naccomplish far more in a limited time.
*sigh* I suppose I ought to take my own\nadvice before leveling it at Basileus.
Thank you for all of your hard work.\nI brought some fresh water.
Thank you, Zena. That's very kind.
With the prince. They're scouting the city\nfor a possible route through the miasma.
He promised to share the results of his\nsearch so that another might take up\nthe fight for Origa after he dies.
It seems your words got through to him.
Well, they'd better have. Traitor or no,\nthat's how an apostle is supposed to be.
If we waste what little time remains to us,\nit means Gabriel and all the other angels\nwill have died in vain.
She was like a mother to you, wasn't she?
You're acting quite resolute, but I know\nit is so painful to lose a parent.
Yes, but making a show of that pain\nwon't change anything.
Truly? When I lost my own mother,\nI broke down in tears.
I thought of all I had left to say to her.\nOf all the affection I would be missing.\nAfter that, the feelings just...flooded out.
But in the wake of that flood, I found peace\nof mind and the clarity to move forward.
I believe our tears can make us stronger,\nso why not take this brief respite to allow\nyourself to...feel?
Thank you for your thoughts, but I am an\napostle charged with dispensing justice.
As one tasked with giving others hope,\nI cannot permit any weakness to show.
Ah, Zena. It seems this poor dear\nhas lost track of her pet cat.
There's no time to look for her now, child.\nWe must hurry to the ship.
Well, it wouldn't do to leave a precious\nfamily member behind.
Don't worry. I will find Mimi.
The cat was last seen near this sewer\nentrance, right?
Yes. ...Thank you all. I'm sorry to take your\ntime during an emergency.
There's always time for a little bonus\njustice from the Karlsplosion!
Miiimi! Where aaare you?\nIf you can hear us, meow back!
Over there! That must be her!\nCome here, Mimi!
Good, we've got her. Now to get back to—
I hear something... Is someone fighting\ndown here?
Zena, please return the cat to her family.\nWe'll investigate that noise.
That wound was nearly closed until the\nlast scuffle. Still, I cannot tarry here.
Hello, Pinon. And I see you have the\nreinforcements Ramiel asked for.
Wait, so this is one of the angels?\nBut I thought they all...died.
When we intercepted Satan's attack,\nI alone was sent flying by the blast.\nIt took me this long to regain mobility.
But Regina couldn't feel your power\nthrough her Sigil.
The connection grows tenuous when one\nparty is gravely injured. In failing to sense\nit, she erroneously assumed I died.
But I bear more pressing news:\nThe Five Archangels are not dead.
But I watched Gabriel and the others\nall vanish! I SAW it, Sandalphon!
Their physical forms were destroyed, yes.\nAnd the laws of nature demand their souls\nthen return to mana.
But it appears they are desperately\nclinging to existence.
Though faint, I still hear the voices of their\nsouls through the connection we share.
And so long as their souls persist,\nthere exists the possibility of revival.
I now make for a research facility beneath\nChurch Headquarters via an emergency\nroute through these sewers.
Said facility holds the vessels required to\nreconstitute the angels' physical form.\nHowever—
A more detailed explanation will have to\nwait. But as I require additional hands,\nI ask you to accompany me to the lab.
